main event: On February 9, 1959, several residents reported seeing an unidentified flying object in Washington, D.C., described as a bright, elliptical-shaped light.
interesting points: The object moved rapidly and silently across the night sky., A local businessman photographed the object using a 35mm camera., The photograph associated with the sighting showed an unidentified object but lacked clarity., The Air Force's Project Blue Book could not identify the object and classified it as a UFO., The original negative of the photograph was requested for further analysis.
